<TITLE> Ershad motorcade comes under attack </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 29 (bdnews24.com)Six people including MP were injured and seven cars were damaged when the motorcade of Jatiya Party chairman HM Ershad headed for Kurigram came under attack in Rangpur Sunday. Police said a mob launched the attack after a youth was run over by a microbus of the motorcade at around 11am at Kathalbarhi area on Rangpur-Kurigram highway. In a press conference at Kurigram circuit house, Ershad later blamed the ruling party's by-polls candidate Jafar Ali for staging the 'pre-planned' attack . Ali denied his involvement in the attack and said Ershad's allegation was baseless. Ershad demanded punishment to the perpetrators of the attack . "We have informed the prime minister of the matter and are waiting for her response," Ershad said. bdn
